# Wallet Master — architecture (Variant A)

Variant A structural migration (HTTP domain folders, `Data/`, Integrations, index getters) is **complete** (2026-05-28). All new `app/` code must follow the rules below.

One domain = the same namespace segment across all layers (e.g. `Transactions` everywhere, never `Transaction` in one folder and `Transactions` in another).

**Do not introduce:** `app/Services/`, `app/Modules/` (vertical modules), DDD `Domain/Application/Infrastructure` layers, or `app/ViewModels/`.

## Approved `app/` roots

- `Actions/{Domain}/` — use cases (write + read orchestration), `handle()`, no `Http/Resources`
- `Data/{Domain}/` — static form options (`*FormOptions`) and shared DTOs reused across layers; **not** for index read results (use Action getters)
- `Http/Controllers|Requests|Resources/{Domain}/` — web layer only
- `Support/{Domain}/` — stateless domain algorithms (no HTTP, no SDK clients)
- `Integrations/{Name}/` — external clients and infrastructure repositories (e.g. Typesense, DescriptionMemory)
- `Imports/` — import workflow (`Workflow/`), bank adapters (`BankAdapters/`), matchers; root unchanged
- `Models/`, `Policies/`, `Jobs/`, `Events/`, `Listeners/`, `Enums/`, `Console/`

Static form data (enums, icons) → `Data/`. Lists from DB → Action getters, controller maps via Resource. Index filters/sort/page → `*IndexRequest`, never `Data/`.

## Domain names (always plural in folders)

`Accounts`, `Transactions`, `Transfers`, `Imports`, `Auth`, `Settings`

| Domain | Example models |
|--------|----------------|
| Accounts | Account, AccountBalanceAdjustment |
| Transactions | Transaction |
| Transfers | (logic on Transaction) |
| Imports | Import |
| Auth | User |
| Settings | User (profile, password) |

## Layer responsibilities

| Layer | Does | Does not |
|-------|------|----------|
| **Controller** | `authorize*`, call Action, `Inertia::render` / redirect, toast `message_key`, map Action getters via `Http\Resources\*` (`->resolve()`) | `DB::transaction`, dedupe rules, `selectRaw` aggregations, business date parsing, full index query workflow |
| **Form Request** | `rules()`, `authorize()`, filter/sort/page helpers (`getFilters()`, `getData()`, `getSorts()`, `Indexable`) | DB writes |
| **Action** | use-case orchestration: queries, filters, sort, aggregates, pagination; write: `handle(User, array)` → `Model`; read index: `handle(*IndexRequest)` + typed getters | `Http\Resources\*`, `Inertia::render`, `number_format`, `asset()` |
| **Data** | form options (`*FormOptions`), shared immutable DTOs | index read results, `Inertia::render`, Eloquent in DTO classes |
| **Resource** | array shape for Vue/Inertia | authorization, business rules |
| **Support/{Domain}** | pure algorithms (dedupe, relative dates); import helpers e.g. `Support/Imports/AmountParser` | HTTP/SDK clients |
| **Integrations** | API clients, infra repositories | wallet business rules |
| **Imports/** | CSV parse, bank adapters, `CommitImport` workflow, `TransferMatcher` | account CRUD |
| **Job** | queue dispatch, timeout, tags | CSV parsing in controller |
| **Policy** | `view` / `update` / `delete` per model | field validation |
| **Model** | relations, `casts()`, general scopes (`whereBelongsTo`) | full index workflow (date filters + sort + aggregates) |

## Data flow

- **Write:** `Request` → `Action` → `Model` (+ `Support` / `Integrations`) → redirect + toast.
- **Read (index):** `*IndexRequest` → `Action::handle($request)` → getters → **Controller** maps `Http\Resources\*` → Inertia.

Reference implementation: `App\Actions\Transactions\ListTransactions` + `TransactionController::index()`.

## Read index pattern

1. **Request** — validation; `getFilters()` for query constraints; `getData()` for UI state (`sort`, `direction`, `per_page`, `page`); `getSorts()` for Eloquent (`sort_by`, `sort_direction`).
2. **Action** — `handle(*IndexRequest $request): void`; call `setSorts()` on the request when needed; store merged UI filters (`getFilters()` + `getData()`); run queries; expose **getters** (e.g. `getFilters()`, `getTransactionPaginator()`, `getAccounts()`, `getSummary()`).
3. **Controller** — single `handle()` call; assemble Inertia props explicitly from getters + Resources (see `TransactionController::index()`).

Action uses `$request->getFilters()` / `getSorts()` for queries; `getFilters()` returns the merged array (`getFilters()` + `getData()`) for the frontend.

**Rules:** one `handle()` per Action instance (fresh DI per request); getter names describe what they return (`getTransactionPaginator`, not `getData()`).

## Code conventions

- Action: one public `handle()`, prefer `final`.
- Write Actions: `handle(User $user, array $validated)` (or model + validated) → return `Model` / `void`.
- Read-index Actions: `handle(*IndexRequest $request): void` + typed getters; **may** import `App\Http\Requests\{Domain}\*`. Do **not** return `Data\*Result` — getters are the canonical pattern.
- Action **never** imports `App\Http\Resources\*`.
- Index filters/sort/page live in `*IndexRequest` (`getFilters()`, `getData()`, `getSorts()`, `Indexable`) — not in `Data/`.
- UI presentation (`asset()`, `label_key`, front-facing date format) only in Resource or Enum metadata.
- Integrations: register bindings in `AppServiceProvider`.
- Tests mirror domains: `tests/Feature/{Domain}/`, `tests/Unit/Data/` or `tests/Unit/Support/{Domain}/`.
- `routes/{domain}.php` where present; on controller moves keep **same URI and route names**.

## Antipatterns

| Avoid | Why |
|-------|-----|
| `Services/` next to `Actions/` | Duplicate application layer |
| `Http\Resources` inside Action | Hard to test; couples application to HTTP |
| `Data/*Result` for index reads | Use Action getters; controller assembles Inertia props |
| `Support/` for SDK/HTTP clients | Use `Integrations/` |
| Big-bang rename of all of `app/` | Review/git conflict risk |
| Changing URLs when moving controllers | Breaks bookmarks and E2E tests |

## Architecture refactors (PR discipline)

- One **domain** or one **concern** per PR; do not mix unrelated feature work unless the same files require it.
- Preserve named routes and URIs when relocating controllers.
- Verification: `wallet-dev-workflow.mdc` (Pint + Sail tests, domain `--filter`).

## Front (Inertia + Vue)

- `resources/js/pages/{domain}/` ↔ `Inertia::render('{domain}/...')`
- Domain UI in `components/{domain}/` — not in `components/ui/`
- Toast i18n keys: `{domain}.toast.*` in `locales/*.json`

## Where to put a new file

| Need… | Location |
|-------|----------|
| Inertia endpoint | `Http/Controllers/{Domain}/` |
| Request validation | `Http/Requests/{Domain}/` |
| JSON props shape | `Http/Resources/{Domain}/` |
| Inertia index props (getters → Resource mapping) | `Http/Controllers/{Domain}/` |
| Business operation | `Actions/{Domain}/` |
| Read list orchestration (`*IndexRequest`, getters) | `Actions/{Domain}/` |
| Form options / shared DTO | `Data/{Domain}/` |
| Index filters, sort, pagination | `Http/Requests/{Domain}/` (*IndexRequest) |
| Domain algorithm | `Support/{Domain}/` |
| Import parse helpers (amount, date, encoding) | `Support/Imports/` |
| External API | `Integrations/{Name}/` |
| DB entity | `Models/` |
| CSV import workflow / bank adapter | `Imports/Workflow/`, `Imports/BankAdapters/` |
| Queue job | `Jobs/` + dispatch from Action/Workflow |
| HTTP test | `tests/Feature/{Domain}/` |
| Pure logic test | `tests/Unit/...` |
